sorry about the double post but I’ve just realized that wallet will come at a lost to platform owner because of payment gateway fees. In my case Stripe will charge 2.9% + .30cents + 1DOP currency exchange rate. So a mechanism where we can add fees on top of the TopUp amount would be great.Edit: I achieved it by modifying the user_wallet_balance_screen.dart. with the following code for anyone interested (assuming you’re using stripe as payment gateway)// Calculate the total amount with the 3% fee double originalAmount = walletAmountCont.text.toDouble(); double feeAmount = originalAmount * 0.03; // 3% fee double totalAmount = originalAmount + feeAmount; StripeServiceNew stripeServiceNew = StripeServiceNew( isTest: currentPaymentMethod!.isTest == 1, stripePaymentKey: key, stripeURL: stripeURL, totalAmount: totalAmount, stripePaymentPublishKey: stripePaymentPublishKey, onComplete: (p0) { Map req = { “amount”: totalAmount, // Use the total amount with the fee “transaction_type”: PAYMENT_METHOD_STRIPE, “transaction_id”: p0[‘transaction_id’] };walletTopUp(req);
